text: This movie has you cheering for the bad guy every chance you get. I saw this last night, the critics are hating on it for some good reasons. The movie is very sloppy, too many sub plots, the plot is over complicated, but the Kevin Costner story with him having his memories changed is SOOO Good. I have a Video review on my channel that I go into more depth in. Overall though I would say this isn't a good movie but it does have an amazing story in it about a murderer who gets a memory transfer so all of the sudden he starts caring about some people in society. It is a very interesting concept that I wish was executed a lot better with no stupid sub plots.
